# Website Page Title via react-helmet-async

Applies when authoring or editing a website route page (`website/src/app/ui/pages/**/*.tsx`) or its top-level screen component.

## Rule

Every website route page that has a meaningful screen MUST set a per-page document `<title>` by rendering `<Helmet><title>{...}</title></Helmet>` inside the page's screen component, using a **page-scoped translation key**.

`react-helmet-async` is already installed and wired in `MyApp` (`website/src/app/ui/base/core/MyApp.tsx`):

```tsx
<Helmet defaultTitle={t("title")} titleTemplate={`${t("title")} | %s`}/>
```

So a page that renders `<title>مرحبًا بك في اجتماع</title>` produces a browser tab title of `<app title> | مرحبًا بك في اجتماع`. Pages that render no `<Helmet><title>` fall back to `defaultTitle` (the app title) — acceptable for stubs, but real screens should set their own.

## How to comply

1. Add a `title` key to the page's scoped translation namespace in **both** `ar.ts` and `en.ts` (W14: mirror every key or `yarn type-check` fails).
2. In the screen component, bind the translator at the page namespace node and render:

```tsx
import {Helmet} from "react-helmet-async";
const t = useTranslator(t => t.ui.pages.<area>.<page>);
// ...
<Helmet><title>{t("title")}</title></Helmet>
```

3. Do not hardcode the title literal in JSX — it must come from the scoped translator (W14 item 5: bound nested translator, no dotted runtime strings, no raw product copy).

## Canonical case

`CustomerHomeScreen` (`website/src/app/ui/components/customer/home/CustomerHomeScreen.tsx`) reads `t.ui.pages.customer.home.title` = "مرحبًا بك في اجتماع" / "Welcome to Ejtmaa" and renders `<Helmet><title>{t("title")}</title></Helmet>`. See `docs/platforms/website/flow-customer-shell.md`.

## What is NOT required

A `null`-stub page (`Main()` returns `null`) does not need a title — `defaultTitle` covers it. Add the title in the same task that ships the screen composition.

## Authority

- `website/src/app/ui/base/core/MyApp.tsx` (`<Helmet defaultTitle ... titleTemplate ...>`)
- `website/src/app/ui/components/customer/home/CustomerHomeScreen.tsx` (canonical case)
- `website/src/resources/translations/ar.ts` / `en.ts` (`ui.pages.customer.home.title`)
- `docs/platforms/website/flow-customer-shell.md`
